The Caped Crusader of the hugely popular DC Comics story has been a favourite among comic fans throughout generations. Robert Pattinson stepped into the Paris Premiere as the new Batman after the torch had been passed down by star actors like Michael Keaton, Christian Bale and Ben Affleck. With The Batman premiering in France, the Paris Saint-Germain superstar Neymar did not miss the opportunity to attend before the movie released worldwide. The Brazilian forward has always been a Batman fan, with a tattoo on his back dedicated to his superhero.   Alaafin’s estranged Queen confirms surgery     Zlatan Ibile flaunts second baby, vows eight more     Seven popular musicians who changed stage names   - Advertisement - Neymar surprised fans by attending “The Batman” premier alongside cast members, Robert Pattinson and Zoe Kravitz following Pattison’s personalized birthday messages inviting him for the event, sent earlier this month. Sharing photos from the premiere, the PSG star wrote: “About tonight @batman.” Director, Matt Reeves also posted pictures of the footballer enjoying his time at the premiere with the actors as well as getting an opportunity to sit in the iconic batmobile.